SIMPLE: hobnail
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hobnail
<hw>Hob"nail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st <ets>hob +
nail</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A short, sharp-pointed, large-headed
nail, -- used in shoeing houses and for studding the soles of heavy
shoes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clownish person; a rustic.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hobnail liver</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a disease
in which the liver is shrunken, hard, and covered with projections like
hobnails; one of the forms of cirrhosis of the liver.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hobnail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hobnail
<hw>Hob"nail`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To tread down roughly, as with
hobnailed shoes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your rights and charters <qex>hobnailed</qex> into slush.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hobnailed</ent>⟦br⟧
